content:
Standard opportunity reports help you report on your opportunity pipeline and history, opportunity sources, opportunity types, and more.

In the Folders pane on the Reports tab, select Opportunity Reports.
Click the report you want.
REPORT NAME	DESCRIPTION
Closed Opportunities	Won opportunities
Opportunities by Type	Types of available opportunities.
Opportunity Field History	Field history on opportunities. Available only if your organization tracks this information.
Opportunities with Opportunity and Product Splits	
Opportunity History	Status changes on opportunities. Available only if your organization tracks this information.
Opportunity Pipeline Trend	A historical snapshot of your opportunities; opportunity amounts are grouped by historical stage for specified months.
Opportunity Pipeline	Opportunities by stage.
Opportunity Pipeline with Splits	Opportunities summarized by split information such as assigned user and percentage.
Opportunity Product	Opportunities by month and product.
Opportunity Sources	Sources of your opportunities.
Opportunity Stage Duration	Duration of an opportunity at each stage.
Opportunity Teams	Information about opportunities and opportunity teams to which you belong.

You can also summarize information for these reports by various fields, including Split Total Price, Split Expected Product Amount, and more. 

See Opportunity Report Types and Tips for Working with Opportunity Reports.
title: Standard Opportunity Reports in Salesforce
